@0xced commented on [Tue May 08 2018](https://github.com/NuGet/Home/issues/6921#issuecomment-387541961)

The linked blog post explains why the HttpClient is used this way:
> It's very important to create a new instance of HttpClient for the each iteration: otherwise, the connection will be reused, and we will not get such a picture.


